    </div>

    <p class="text-gray-300">summed over the demanded range for <span class="math">k</span>. Then, bounding the probability <span class="math">\\varepsilon_{1}(n,m,d)</span> will yield the specific choice of <span class="math">d</span>. For estimating the probability that a random left-sided <span class="math">d</span>-regular graph <span class="math">\\Gamma</span> is not a <span class="math">b(k)</span>-expander, Brakedown uses the <em>double-union bound</em></p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto my-4">

      <table class="min-w-full text-sm text-gray-300">

