    <p class="text-gray-300">4.3 Putting the pieces together</p>

    <p class="text-gray-300">We assume a code with constant rate <span class="math">\\rho=\\frac{n_{k}}{N_{k}}</span> and <span class="math">K\\geq 1</span> recursion steps with constant scaling factor <span class="math">\\alpha=\\frac{N_{k}}{N_{k+1}}</span>, starting from an arbitrary linear code <span class="math">E_{0}:F^{n_{0}}\\to F^{N_{0}}</span> of rate <span class="math">\\rho</span> and minimal distance <span class="math">&gt;\\delta</span>. Given security parameter <span class="math">\\lambda</span> we determine the row-weights <span class="math">c_{k}</span>, <span class="math">d_{k}</span> for the matrices <span class="math">A_{k},B_{k}</span>, <span class="math">k=1,\\ldots,K</span>, such that</p>

    <p class="text-gray-300"><span class="math">\\sum_{k=0}^{K-1}\\sum_{i=1,2}\\varepsilon_{i}^{(A)}(n_{k}^{(A)},m_{k}^{(A)},c_{k})+\\varepsilon_{i}^{(B)}(n_{k}^{(B)},m_{k}^{(B)},d_{k})\\leq 2^{-\\lambda},</span> (18)</p>

